2 unit(s) Chicken Breasts
100 g Bacon Strips
1 unit(s) Ciabatta Roll
1 unit(s) Gooseberries
1 unit(s) Mini Cucumber
56 g Spring Mix
¼ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
2 tbsp Apricot Spread
½ tbsp White Wine Vinegar
7 g Zesty Garlic Blend
2 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 450°F.
Wash and dry all produce.
Cut ciabatta roll into 1-inch pieces.
On a parchment-lined baking sheet, toss ciabatta pieces with 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then season with salt, pepper and half the Zesty Garlic Blend. Toast in the top of the oven 5-6 min, stirring halfway through, until lightly golden.

Meanwhile, peel, then halve gooseberries.
Halve cucumber lengthwise. Cut into 1/4-inch half moons.

On a separate cutting board, pat chicken dry with paper towels. Season with salt, pepper and remaining Zesty Garlic Blend.
Wrap 2 bacon strips around each piece of c hicken. (TIP: Overlapping strips by 1 inch helps keep bacon on chicken.)
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high.
When the pan is hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then chicken. Pan-fry 2-3 min per side, until golden.
Remove from heat, then transfer chicken to an unlined baking sheet.

Roast in the bottom of the oven 14-18 min, until cooked through.**
When done, brush bacon-wrapped chicken with half the apricot spread.

Meanwhile, in a large bowl, whisk together half the vinegar (use all for 4 servings), remaining apricot spread and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil. Season with salt and pepper.

When chicken is almost done, add ciabatta croutons, spring mix, cucumbers and gooseberries to the bowl with dressing. Toss to combine.
Thinly slice chicken.
Divide chicken and salad between plates.
Sprinkle feta over top of salad.